class Solution {
    public boolean canTransform(String start, String result) {
        int n = start.length();
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < n || j < n) {
            while (i < n && start.charAt(i) == 'X') i++;
            while (j < n && result.charAt(j) == 'X') j++;
            if (i == n && j == n) return true;
            if (i == n || j == n) return false;
            if (start.charAt(i) != result.charAt(j)) return false;
            if (start.charAt(i) == 'L' && i < j) return false;
            if (start.charAt(i) == 'R' && i > j) return false;
            i++; j++;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Two-pointer sweep skips all 'X' characters and verifies that the non-'X' sequences of start and result are identical. For each 'L' in start its index must be ≥ its index in result (L can only move left), and for each 'R' its index must be ≤ its index in result (R can only move right). Single pass, constant extra space.

